":[{"name":"Buck","meanings":["English: nickname from Middle English <i>buc(ke)</i> ‘male goat’ (Old English <i>bucca</i>) or a ‘male deer’ (Old English <i>bucc</i>). The goat was popularly associated with lecherous behaviour and the deer with timidity and speed. The surname may also be a shortened form of longer occupational names, for example Roger <i>le Bucmanger'</i> ‘dealer in bucks or venison’, (Warwickshire 1221) or Walter <i>Bucswayn</i> perhaps ‘goatherd’ (Somerset 1327).","English: topographic name for someone who lived near a prominent beech tree, such as <i>Peter atte Buk</i> (Suffolk 1327), from Middle English <i>buk</i> ‘beech’ (from Old English <i>bōc</i>).","German and Dutch (Limburg): from a personal name, a short form of <i>Burkhard</i> (see   Burkhart  )."]}]},{"name":"John","type":"FIRST","meanings":["Greek: the Lord gave graciously; whom Jehovah gave; whom Jehovah bestowed."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"John Bucke was born in 1290, in England, United Kingdom. He married Isabell Richardson about 1311. They were the parents of at least 1 son."},"et":{"1290–":"1290–Surnud","1290–Female":"1290–Surnud","1315–1340":"1315–1340","1290–Male":"1290–Surnud","1315":"1315","1340":"1340","about 1311":"umbes 1311","1290":"1290","England, United Kingdom":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Kempsey, Worcestershire, England":"Kempsey, Worcestershire, England"},"fi":{"1290–":"1290–Kuollut","1290–Female":"1290–Kuollut","1315–1340":"1315–1340","1290–Male":"1290–Kuollut","1315":"1315","1340":"1340","about 1311":"noin 1311","1290":"1290","England, United Kingdom":"Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Kempsey, Worcestershire, England":"Kempsey, Worcestershire, England"},"fr":{"1290–":"1290–Décédé","1290–Female":"1290–Décédée","1315–1340":"1315–1340","1290–Male":"1290–Décédé","1315":"1315","1340":"1340","about 1311":"environ 1311","1290":"1290","England, United Kingdom":"Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Kempsey, Worcestershire, England":"Kempsey, Worcestershire, Angleterre","lifeS